<span id="freeTextContainer1069105861984143063">An amoral story about class and gender in turn of the century Paris. The main character, nicknamed Bel-Ami, climbs the social ladder by being a heartless cad who objectifies all women and despises all men in jealousy or disgust. He succeeds too. Not a feel good story but a believable one that in a strange way imagined a newspaper that reminded my of Fox News--partnering with politicians to spin stories as propaganda and help its owners become wealthier. The way the arrogant main character treate</span>
  <span id="freeText1069105861984143063" style="display:none">An amoral story about class and gender in turn of the century Paris. The main character, nicknamed Bel-Ami, climbs the social ladder by being a heartless cad who objectifies all women and despises all men in jealousy or disgust. He succeeds too. Not a feel good story but a believable one that in a strange way imagined a newspaper that reminded my of Fox News--partnering with politicians to spin stories as propaganda and help its owners become wealthier. The way the arrogant main character treated all people as means to his ends with zero empathy also stands as a shockingly accurate prediction of Trump. Isn't it sad when stereotypes (men are pigs who care about nothing but power) turns out to be true?</span>
